<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="411" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/485</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-21T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            21, 1918—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5684. Repeat your 5110, September 18, 11 p.m., regarding Siberian
                                Railway to London and Rome. At same time inquire whether French
                                Government would be willing to instruct its representatives in Great
                                Britain, [Italy], Japan, China, and Vladivostok of its views on this
                                question. If so, request that they do so.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>